article.headline: New Orleans 85, Texas St. 81
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas -- Charles Carmouche hit two free throws with 18 seconds left Monday night as New Orleans defeated Texas State 85-81. Brandon Bush made a layup with 35 seconds left to pull Texas State (3-6) to within one at 82-81. But New Orleans hit three free throws the rest of the way for the final margin. Kyndall Dykes and T.J. Worley each scored 19 points for New Orleans (4-5). Darrian McKinstry added 18 points, 15 of those on 3-pointers. Ty Gough led Texas State with 16 points. John Rybak and Bush each had 15 points. New Orleans led 34-33 at the half. The game was tied 18 times.
